==English==
[[Image:Dale Earnhardt Jr car2006.jpg|thumb|300px|Dale Earnhardt, Jr.'s [[NASCAR]] team executes a pitstop]]
===Etymology===
Literally, a [[stop]] at the [[pit]] of an automobile race track.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈpɪt.stɑp/

===Noun===
# A stop made during an automobile race at the [[pit]] to refuel and perform other periodic maintance on the vehicle.
# A brief stop for fuel, rest, and refreshment during an automobile journey.

